#compdef aer
# =============================================================================
# aer — aurae-runtime/aurae's REMOTE CLIENT
#   CLI for the AURAE distributed-systems
#   runtime daemon (`auraed`).  Aurae is a
#   memory-safe Rust DAEMON + PROCESS MANAGER +
#   PID-1 INIT replacement that schedules
#   processes, containers, and virtual
#   machines on a node, and exposes them via
#   a gRPC API so that higher-order
#   orchestrators (Kubernetes, Nomad, custom
#   distributed schedulers) can drive
#   workloads down to the socket layer.
#   `aer` is the operator-facing gRPC CLIENT
#   for talking to `auraed`.  Built on direct
#   `tonic` — the canonical Rust gRPC
#   framework from the Tokio ecosystem.
#   Rust=110 leader bump opening Axis 55.
#
# AXIS 55 — gRPC FRAMEWORK — OPENS @ R809
# ========================================
# Establishes the 55th three-language axis in
# the corpus.  This axis covers CLI tools
# written in language X that ship a DIRECT
# library binding to a gRPC client + server
# framework.  Canonical implementations per
# language:
#   * Rust       : tonic (this entry)
#                  — hyperium/tonic.
#                    ~10.7k stars on GitHub.
#                    Apache 2.0.  Built on
#                    top of `hyper`,
#                    `tower`, `tokio` for
#                    full async + streaming
#                    + interceptor support.
#                    Used by Linkerd,
#                    Fluvio, Quickwit, Iroh,
#                    Apache OpenDAL,
#                    InfluxDB IOx, and dozens
#                    of other production
#                    Rust gRPC deployments
#                  — direct dep at
#                    `aurae-runtime/aurae`
#                    workspace.dependencies
#                    line:
#                    `tonic = ...`
#   * Go         : google.golang.org/grpc —
#                  the OFFICIAL Google-
#                  maintained Go gRPC
#                  framework.  Canonical
#                  reference implementation.
#                  R810 will close the Go
#                  side
#   * TS-Node    : @grpc/grpc-js — the
#                  OFFICIAL Google-maintained
#                  pure-JavaScript gRPC
#                  client + server.  R811
#                  will close the TS-Node
#                  side
#
# Distinguishing aer / Aurae from sibling
# corpus runtime-orchestration tooling:
#   - CONTAINERD (`_ctr`, `_containerd`):
#     OCI container runtime.  Aurae is a
#     LOWER-LEVEL PID-1 + process manager
#     that can DRIVE containerd as one of
#     several workload backends
#   - CRI-O (`_crio`): also a container
#     runtime.  Same scope as containerd
#   - PODMAN (`_podman`): docker-compatible
#     container manager.  Higher-level
#     than Aurae
#   - KUBERNETES (`_kubectl`): cluster
#     orchestrator that talks to a node
#     agent (kubelet).  Aurae positions
#     itself as a kubelet REPLACEMENT
#     (or sibling) that exposes a richer
#     gRPC API + lets the kubelet talk to
#     it
#   - NOMAD (`_nomad`): HashiCorp's
#     workload scheduler.  Driver-agnostic.
#     Aurae complements rather than
#     replaces
#   - SYSTEMD (`_systemctl`): traditional
#     init+process manager.  Aurae aims to
#     replace systemd-as-PID-1 for
#     distributed-systems-shaped workloads
#   - FIRECRACKER (`_firecracker`): AWS
#     VMM for micro-VMs.  Aurae's `vm`
#     subcommand wraps Firecracker as one
#     of its VM backends
#
# KEY AURAE FEATURES:
#   - MEMORY-SAFE PID-1 — written entirely
#     in Rust, no C dependencies in the
#     hot path.  Reduces the attack
#     surface of the most-privileged
#     process on a Linux node
#   - gRPC EVERYTHING — `auraed` exposes
#     every workload operation (allocate
#     cell, start executable, allocate
#     VM, etc.) over a tonic gRPC service.
#     `aer` is one of three first-party
#     clients (alongside `auraescript`
#     for V8-scripted control and the
#     Rust `client` crate)
#   - CELLS — Aurae's primary scheduling
#     unit.  A "cell" is a cgroup v2
#     container with configurable CPU
#     weight, CPU max, CPU+memory sets,
#     process isolation, and network
#     isolation.  Hosts one or more
#     "executables" (user-defined
#     processes)
#   - FIRECRACKER VMS — `aer vm allocate`
#     spawns a Firecracker micro-VM with
#     a kernel image, root drive,
#     additional drive mounts, kernel
#     boot args, and optional nested
#     `auraed` connection for VM-internal
#     orchestration
#   - DISCOVERY SERVICE — `auraed`
#     publishes its presence + service
#     directory to other Aurae nodes for
#     cross-node service discovery
#   - OBSERVABILITY STREAMS — every
#     subprocess exposes a streaming gRPC
#     endpoint for stdin/stdout/stderr
#     (selectable via channel_type:
#     1=stdout, 2=stderr).  `aer observe
#     get-sub-process-stream` consumes
#     these in real time
#   - HEALTH CHECKS — Aurae implements
#     the gRPC reflection + health
#     protocol so any standard gRPC tool
#     (grpcurl, grpcui) can introspect
#     and probe a live `auraed`
#   - PROTOC-FREE BUILD — uses
#     `prost-build` via Tonic's build
#     macros, so contributors don't need
#     a separate `protoc` install.  Protos
#     in `api/v0/{cells,discovery,observe,
#     vms}.proto` are compiled into Rust
#     at workspace build time
#
# CLI ARGUMENT PARSER — clap 4.3 derive
# (`clap = { version = "4.3.21", features
# = ["derive"] }` per workspace.dependencies)
#
# TOP-LEVEL SUBCOMMANDS (verbatim from
# `aer/src/bin/main.rs` `Commands` enum):
#   * cell        Manage Aurae cells
#                 (allocate / free / start /
#                 stop)
#   * discovery   Service discovery
#                 operations
#   * health      gRPC health-check probe
#                 (Health protocol +
#                 reflection)
#   * observe     Observability streams
#                 (get-sub-process-stream)
#   * vm          Firecracker virtual
#                 machine management
#                 (allocate / free / start /
#                 stop)
#
# CELL SUBCOMMANDS:
#   * allocate <CELL_NAME>                 create
#                                          a new
#                                          cgroup-
#                                          backed
#                                          cell
#       --cpu-weight <N>                  cgroup
#                                          cpu.weight
#       --cpu-max <STR>                   cgroup
#                                          cpu.max
#                                          (e.g.
#                                          "200000
#                                          100000")
#       --cpuset-cpus <STR>               cgroup
#                                          cpuset.
#                                          cpus
#                                          (e.g.
#                                          "0-3")
#       --cpuset-mems <STR>               cgroup
#                                          cpuset.
#                                          mems
#       --cell-isolate-process            PID
#                                          namespace
#                                          isolation
#                                          (default
#                                          false)
#       --cell-isolate-network            network
#                                          namespace
#                                          isolation
#                                          (default
#                                          false)
#   * free <CELL_NAME>                     destroy
#                                          a cell
#                                          (frees
#                                          cgroup)
#   * start <CELL_NAME> <EXECUTABLE_NAME>
#                                          launch
#                                          an
#                                          executable
#                                          inside
#                                          a cell
#       -c/--command/--cmd <CMD>          executable
#                                          command
#                                          string
#                                          (required)
#       --description/--desc <DESC>       freeform
#                                          description
#   * stop <CELL_NAME> <EXECUTABLE_NAME>   terminate
#                                          an
#                                          executable
#
# VM SUBCOMMANDS:
#   * allocate <MACHINE_ID>                create
#                                          Firecracker
#                                          micro-VM
#       --mem-size-mb <N>                 RAM in MiB
#                                          (default
#                                          512)
#       --vcpu-count <N>                  vCPUs
#                                          (default
#                                          1)
#       --kernel-img-path <PATH>          REQUIRED;
#                                          path to
#                                          uncompressed
#                                          ELF kernel
#       --kernel-args <STR>               kernel
#                                          command
#                                          line
#                                          (Append
#                                          flag,
#                                          repeatable)
#       --root-drive-path <PATH>          REQUIRED;
#                                          rootfs
#                                          image
#       --root-drive-readonly             mount
#                                          rootfs
#                                          read-only
#       --drive-mount-path <PATH>         extra
#                                          drive
#                                          image
#       --drive-mount-vm-path <PATH>      mount
#                                          point
#                                          in the
#                                          guest
#       --drive-mount-fs-type <TYPE>      ext4 |
#                                          xfs |
#                                          ...
#       --drive-mount-readonly            extra
#                                          drive
#                                          read-only
#       --auraed-address <HOST:PORT>      nested
#                                          auraed
#                                          gRPC
#                                          address
#                                          for
#                                          guest
#                                          control
#   * free <VM_ID>                         destroy
#                                          a VM
#   * start <VM_ID>                        boot a VM
#   * stop <VM_ID>                         shutdown
#                                          a VM
#
# OBSERVE SUBCOMMANDS:
#   * get-sub-process-stream <PROCESS_ID>
#       --channel-type <N>                channel
#                                          type:
#                                          0=stdin
#                                          1=stdout
#                                          (default)
#                                          2=stderr
#
# CRITICAL DIRECT DEPENDENCIES (from
# Cargo.toml workspace.dependencies +
# aer/Cargo.toml):
#   - tonic                    — Rust gRPC
#                                framework
#                                [AXIS 55 LIBRARY]
#   - tokio (with rt-multi-    — async runtime
#     thread + macros)
#   - clap 4.3 (derive)        — CLI parser
#   - anyhow                   — error
#                                handling
#   - futures-util             — async
#                                stream
#                                helpers
#   - client (workspace path)  — Aurae gRPC
#                                client
#                                wrapper crate
#                                (consumes
#                                tonic
#                                generated
#                                stubs)
#   - chrono                   — timestamp
#                                formatting
#   - fancy-regex 0.14         — extended
#                                regex
#                                support
#                                (PCRE-style
#                                lookaround +
#                                backrefs)
#   - proto (workspace path)   — generated
#                                gRPC proto
#                                stubs
#                                produced
#                                by tonic-
#                                build at
#                                workspace
#                                compile
#                                time
#
# Rust 2024 edition.  Apache-2.0.  Workspace
# contains five binaries: `aer` (CLI), `auraed`
# (daemon), `auraescript` (V8 control plane),
# `client` (library), plus `proto` (generated
# stubs) and `ebpf-shared` (eBPF helper
# types)
#
# UPSTREAM:
#   * Source             : https://github.com/aurae-runtime/aurae
#   * Site               : https://aurae.io
#   * Foundation         : https://nivenly.org (parent foundation)
#   * tonic              : https://github.com/hyperium/tonic
#   * FOSDEM 2023 talk   : https://fosdem.org/2023/schedule/event/rust_aurae_a_new_pid_1_for_distributed_systems/
#   * License            : Apache-2.0
#   * Founder            : Kris Nóva (krisnova@nivenly.com)
#
# INSTALL:
#   # From source
#   git clone https://github.com/aurae-runtime/aurae
#   cd aurae
#   make all
#   sudo make install
#
#   # Or cargo install just the CLI
#   cargo install --git https://github.com/aurae-runtime/aurae \
#       --bin aer aer
#
# USAGE EXAMPLES:
#
#   # Cell management
#
#   # Allocate a cell with 50% CPU weight + CPU pinning
#   aer cell allocate my-cell \
#       --cpu-weight 50 \
#       --cpuset-cpus 0-3 \
#       --cell-isolate-process \
#       --cell-isolate-network
#
#   # Free a cell
#   aer cell free my-cell
#
#   # Start an executable inside a cell
#   aer cell start my-cell my-app \
#       -c "/usr/bin/myapp --flag value" \
#       --description "My production app"
#
#   # Stop an executable
#   aer cell stop my-cell my-app
#
#   # VM management (Firecracker)
#
#   # Allocate a 2-vCPU 2 GiB micro-VM
#   aer vm allocate my-vm \
#       --vcpu-count 2 \
#       --mem-size-mb 2048 \
#       --kernel-img-path /var/lib/aurae/vmlinux \
#       --kernel-args "console=ttyS0" \
#       --kernel-args "reboot=k" \
#       --root-drive-path /var/lib/aurae/rootfs.ext4 \
#       --auraed-address 192.168.0.10:8080
#
#   # Boot the VM
#   aer vm start my-vm
#
#   # Stop + free
#   aer vm stop my-vm
#   aer vm free my-vm
#
#   # Observe a subprocess's stdout stream
#   aer observe get-sub-process-stream 12345 \
#       --channel-type 1
#
#   # Health probe (gRPC standard Health
#   # protocol)
#   aer health
#
#   # Service discovery
#   aer discovery
#
#   # Help (clap default)
#   aer --help
#   aer cell --help
#   aer vm allocate --help
#
# OPTIONS (sourced directly from
# https://github.com/aurae-runtime/aurae/blob/main/aer/src/bin/main.rs Cli/Commands +
# aer/src/{runtime,discovery,grpc,observe,vms}/*.rs subcommand! macro invocations):
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

local -a _aer_commands
_aer_commands=(
    'cell:Manage Aurae cells (cgroup-backed process containers)'
    'discovery:Service discovery operations against auraed'
    'health:gRPC standard Health-protocol probe'
    'observe:Observability streams (subprocess stdin/stdout/stderr tail)'
    'vm:Firecracker virtual machine management'
    'help:Print help for a command'
)

local -a _aer_cell_actions
_aer_cell_actions=(
    'allocate:Create a new cgroup-backed cell with resource limits and isolation flags'
    'free:Destroy a cell and free its cgroup'
    'start:Launch an executable inside a cell'
    'stop:Terminate a running executable in a cell'
)

local -a _aer_vm_actions
_aer_vm_actions=(
    'allocate:Allocate a Firecracker micro-VM with kernel + drive image'
    'free:Destroy a VM definition'
    'start:Boot a VM'
    'stop:Shutdown a VM'
)

local -a _aer_observe_actions
_aer_observe_actions=(
    'get-sub-process-stream:Stream a subprocess channel (stdin/stdout/stderr)'
)

_arguments -C \
    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
    '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
    '(-): :->command' \
    '(-)*:: :->args' \
    && ret=0

case $state in
    command)
        _describe -t commands 'aer command' _aer_commands && ret=0
        ;;
    args)
        case $line[1] in
            cell)
                _arguments -C \
                    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help for cell]' \
                    '(-): :->cellaction' \
                    '(-)*:: :->cellargs' \
                    && ret=0
                case $state in
                    cellaction)
                        _describe -t actions 'cell action' _aer_cell_actions && ret=0 ;;
                    cellargs)
                        case $line[1] in
                            allocate)
                                _arguments \
                                    '--cpu-weight=[cgroup cpu.weight value]:n: ' \
                                    '--cpu-max=[cgroup cpu.max value]:str: ' \
                                    '--cpuset-cpus=[cgroup cpuset.cpus]:cpu-set: ' \
                                    '--cpuset-mems=[cgroup cpuset.mems]:mem-set: ' \
                                    '--cell-isolate-process[create PID namespace isolation]' \
                                    '--cell-isolate-network[create network namespace isolation]' \
                                    '1:cell name:' \
                                    && ret=0 ;;
                            free)
                                _arguments \
                                    '1:cell name:' \
                                    && ret=0 ;;
                            start)
                                _arguments \
                                    '(-c --command --cmd)'{-c+,--command=,--cmd=}'[executable command string (required)]:cmd: ' \
                                    '(--description --desc)--description=[executable description]:desc: ' \
                                    '(--description --desc)--desc=[alias for --description]:desc: ' \
                                    '1:cell name:' \
                                    '2:executable name:' \
                                    && ret=0 ;;
                            stop)
                                _arguments \
                                    '1:cell name:' \
                                    '2:executable name:' \
                                    && ret=0 ;;
                        esac
                        ;;
                esac
                ;;
            vm)
                _arguments -C \
                    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help for vm]' \
                    '(-): :->vmaction' \
                    '(-)*:: :->vmargs' \
                    && ret=0
                case $state in
                    vmaction)
                        _describe -t actions 'vm action' _aer_vm_actions && ret=0 ;;
                    vmargs)
                        case $line[1] in
                            allocate)
                                _arguments \
                                    '--mem-size-mb=[RAM in MiB (default 512)]:mb: ' \
                                    '--vcpu-count=[vCPU count (default 1)]:n: ' \
                                    '--kernel-img-path=[REQUIRED: path to kernel image]:path:_files' \
                                    '*--kernel-args=[kernel command line argument (repeatable)]:arg: ' \
                                    '--root-drive-path=[REQUIRED: rootfs image path]:path:_files' \
                                    '--root-drive-readonly[mount rootfs read-only]' \
                                    '--drive-mount-path=[additional drive image path]:path:_files' \
                                    '--drive-mount-vm-path=[guest mount point]:path: ' \
                                    '--drive-mount-fs-type=[filesystem type (ext4/xfs/...)]:fs: ' \
                                    '--drive-mount-readonly[mount additional drive read-only]' \
                                    '--auraed-address=[nested auraed gRPC address (host:port)]:addr: ' \
                                    '1:machine id:' \
                                    && ret=0 ;;
                            free|start|stop)
                                _arguments \
                                    '1:vm id:' \
                                    && ret=0 ;;
                        esac
                        ;;
                esac
                ;;
            observe)
                _arguments -C \
                    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help for observe]' \
                    '(-): :->obsaction' \
                    '(-)*:: :->obsargs' \
                    && ret=0
                case $state in
                    obsaction)
                        _describe -t actions 'observe action' _aer_observe_actions && ret=0 ;;
                    obsargs)
                        case $line[1] in
                            get-sub-process-stream)
                                _arguments \
                                    '--channel-type=[channel: 0=stdin, 1=stdout (default), 2=stderr]:n: ' \
                                    '1:process id:' \
                                    && ret=0 ;;
                        esac
                        ;;
                esac
                ;;
            discovery|health)
                _arguments \
                    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
                    && ret=0
                ;;
            help)
                _arguments \
                    '1:command:(cell discovery health observe vm)' \
                    && ret=0
                ;;
        esac
        ;;
esac

return ret
